  pm-wc1r,related,"2026-07-21T21:51:22.939Z",null,null
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T21:51:22.939Z",codex-root,"Duplicate check: searched all statuses for PM-CLI-2G, merge.pm-item-toon, git config, merge install, and permission denied; no item tracked this exact failure. Live Sentry evidence: PM-CLI-2G is new, unresolved, handled, count 2, first seen 2026-07-21T21:37:22.513Z and last seen 2026-07-21T21:37:23.120Z in @unbrained/pm-cli 2026.7.21. Permalink: https://unbrained.sentry.io/issues/135741631/."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T21:51:22.939Z",codex-root,"Acceptance scope: cover a real temporary Git repository with a deliberately non-writable repository config boundary; assert deterministic error metadata and remediation text; prove no partial merge-driver configuration; preserve successful installation and idempotency; verify telemetry/Sentry classification for expected permission constraints; update merge-safety documentation."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T21:51:22.939Z",codex-root,Permission-constrained Git metadata is a normal execution environment for CI and review sandboxes. Merge-driver setup should distinguish an expected environmental inability to mutate local Git config from an unexpected application defect.
body: ""
